			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I found more endian-dependence. In places it does *(short*)char_ptr = '=' for example, instead of the portable strcpy( char_ptr, "=" ). Or similarly, if ( *(short*)char_ptr == '=' instead of !strcmp( char_ptr, "=" ).
<br />
<br />And then there are the pointer casts, that I haven't figured out yet. Some of them use pointers as booleans, doing char_ptr = (char*) 1 for true, rather than the portable static char true_sentinel; char_ptr = &amp;true_sentinel.
<br />
<br />The twisted nature of these optimizations makes it a kind of interesting project to consider making portable, especially doing so while making minimal modifications.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

