				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">intptr_t just complicates it. Use void* and it works much more smoothly (in C, due to implicit void* conversion), and fully portably:
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">static void* false_ptr = NULL;<br />static void* true_ptr = &amp;true_ptr;<br />static void* po_ptr = &amp;po_ptr;<br /><br />const char* ptr;<br />ptr = false_ptr;<br />assert&#40; !ptr &#41;;<br /><br />ptr = true_ptr;<br />assert&#40; ptr &amp;&amp; ptr == true_ptr &#41;;<br /><br />ptr = &quot;str&quot;;<br />assert&#40; ptr != false_ptr &amp;&amp; ptr != true_ptr &#41;;</div></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
